I also see this behaviour when trying to deploy to GitHub pages (I get a 404 error) - https://github.com/Sparrow0hawk/mynearestwardmarginal-svelte/issues/1

I have only set `paths` in the `svelte.config.js`:
```js
import adapter from '@sveltejs/adapter-static';

/** @type {import('@sveltejs/kit').Config} */
const config = {

	kit: {
		adapter: adapter({
			// default options are shown. On some platforms
			// these options are set automatically — see below
			pages: 'build',
			assets: 'build',
			fallback: null,
			precompress: false,
			strict: true
		}),
		paths: {
			base: process.env.NODE_ENV === "production" ? "/mynearestwardmarginal-svelte" : ""
		}
	}
};

export default config;
```

That repo is using kit version 1.10.0, if I revert to 1.8.8 I get the correct paths.
